Hello everyone,

I'm new in this crawling solution and I set up Heritrix 1.14.4. Crawling a
website works, but when I try to run a job created with the profile (which
was used for crawling the site the 1st time) It stops and I have a lot off
Alerts like this:


Time: 

Dec. 28, 2012 07:21:41 GMT 


Level: 

SEVERE 


Message: 

peekItem failure; retrying (in thread 'ToeThread #48')


Exception: 

com.sleepycat.je.DatabaseException: (JE 3.3.82) bdb queue cap missing

Stacktrace: com.sleepycat.je.DatabaseException: (JE 3.3.82) bdb queue cap
missing

        at
org.archive.crawler.frontier.BdbMultipleWorkQueues.getNextNearestItem(BdbMul
tipleWorkQueues.java:294)

        at
org.archive.crawler.frontier.BdbMultipleWorkQueues.get(BdbMultipleWorkQueues
.java:258)

        at
org.archive.crawler.frontier.BdbWorkQueue.peekItem(BdbWorkQueue.java:107)

        at org.archive.crawler.frontier.WorkQueue.peek(WorkQueue.java:145)

        at
org.archive.crawler.frontier.WorkQueueFrontier.next(WorkQueueFrontier.java:6
51)

        at org.archive.crawler.framework.ToeThread.run(ToeThread.java:147)

 

I didn't set any recrawl option (modules/submodules). The re-crawl works
only if I delete the jdb file from the crawl's state folder.

 

What sould I do/set to be able to re-crawl a website and store it in the
same folder as the 1st crawl? So I will have 00000000.jdb 00000001.jdb
0000002.jdb files in the state folder.

 

Thanks.

Regards,

Ferencz
